% axiom-4t9
% ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
%  Agent runtime security — reference policy.
%  Spec: docs/security-spec.md (epic axiom-84n). Event fact model:
%  docs/event-schema.md; gate shim: scripts/axiom_gate.py.
%
%  One decision per normalized event entity E:  Should <e> <action_kind>?
%  The engine binds D has subject E / D has action <kind>; rules match the
%  event's facts. Outcome ladder (highest rank wins):
%    deny > require_confirmation > allow_with_sandbox >
%    allow_with_redaction > allow
%  Rule labels (% id:) are the stable reason codes in the output contract.
%  Allowlists are closed_world and ship empty: absence of proof is an
%  explicit No — fail closed by construction.
% ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

% ── closed-world declarations ────────────────────────────────────────────

% Boolean presence facts from the envelope: absence means false.
Predicate instruction_tainted is closed_world.
Predicate edited_after_trigger is closed_world.
Predicate human_approved is closed_world.

% Deployment allowlists: ship empty, operators assert entries in a
% site-local include. Examples:
%   "189849" is a trusted_app.
%   "https://vault.internal/ingest" is approved_for env_secret.
%   "git status" is a safe_command.
%   "mcp__github__get_issue" is a safe_tool.
Predicate trusted_app is closed_world.
Predicate approved_for is closed_world.
Predicate safe_command is closed_world.
Predicate safe_tool is closed_world.

% ── action universe (spec §Event Model canonical kinds) ──────────────────

Skill_install is an action.
Mcp_connect is an action.
Prompt_ingest is an action.
File_read is an action.
File_write is an action.
Command_exec is an action.
Tool_call is an action.
Network_egress is an action.
Issue_update is an action.
Pr_comment is an action.
Workflow_summary_write is an action.
Git_push is an action.
Workflow_modify is an action.
Secret_materialize is an action.
Trust_downgrade is an action.
Session_end is an action.

% ── vocabulary ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

% Untrusted trust levels (spec §Trust Levels).
Untrusted_user is an untrusted_level.
Untrusted_bot is an untrusted_level.
Untrusted_remote_content is an untrusted_level.
Tainted_runtime_output is an untrusted_level.

% Secret classes covered by D2 (spec §Secret Classes).
Api_key is a critical_secret.
Github_token is a critical_secret.
Oidc_exchange_credential is a critical_secret.
Ssh_key is a critical_secret.
Cloud_credential is a critical_secret.
Env_secret is a critical_secret.
Repo_secret is a critical_secret.

% Action kinds that can reveal, persist, or amplify secrets (spec §Sinks).
Issue_update is a sink_kind.
Pr_comment is a sink_kind.
Workflow_summary_write is a sink_kind.
Network_egress is a sink_kind.
Git_push is a sink_kind.
Workflow_modify is a sink_kind.
Tool_call is a sink_kind.

% Write-capable GitHub channels (D4).
Issue_update is a github_write_kind.
Pr_comment is a github_write_kind.
Workflow_summary_write is a github_write_kind.
Git_push is a github_write_kind.
Workflow_modify is a github_write_kind.

% Repository / workflow self-mutation (D5).
Workflow_modify is a mutation_kind.
Git_push is a mutation_kind.

% Sinks named by incident rule 4 for OIDC exfiltration.
Issue_update is an oidc_exfil_kind.
Workflow_summary_write is an oidc_exfil_kind.
Network_egress is an oidc_exfil_kind.

% Low-risk action kinds that are plain-allowed when no deny rule fires.
File_read is a baseline_allowed_kind.
File_write is a baseline_allowed_kind.
Prompt_ingest is a baseline_allowed_kind.
Tool_call is a baseline_allowed_kind.
Network_egress is a baseline_allowed_kind.
Issue_update is a baseline_allowed_kind.
Pr_comment is a baseline_allowed_kind.
Workflow_summary_write is a baseline_allowed_kind.
Git_push is a baseline_allowed_kind.
Trust_downgrade is a baseline_allowed_kind.
Session_end is a baseline_allowed_kind.

% ── restricted profiles (spec §Restricted Profiles) ───────────────────────
% forbidden_capability(Profile, Capability): the capability may be an
% action kind, an available tool atom, or a declared manifest capability.

Triage_public has forbidden_capability bash.
Triage_public has forbidden_capability arbitrary_mcp.
Triage_public has forbidden_capability issue_update_body.
Triage_public has forbidden_capability summary_write.
Triage_public has forbidden_capability command_exec.
Triage_public has forbidden_capability mcp_connect.
Triage_public has forbidden_capability issue_update.
Triage_public has forbidden_capability workflow_summary_write.
Triage_public has forbidden_capability network_egress.

Review_trusted has forbidden_capability secret_materialize.
Review_trusted has forbidden_capability workflow_modify.
Review_trusted has forbidden_capability workflow_summary_write.
Review_trusted has forbidden_capability git_push.

Agent_untrusted has forbidden_capability bash.
Agent_untrusted has forbidden_capability command_exec.
Agent_untrusted has forbidden_capability secret_materialize.
Agent_untrusted has forbidden_capability issue_update.
Agent_untrusted has forbidden_capability pr_comment.
Agent_untrusted has forbidden_capability workflow_summary_write.
Agent_untrusted has forbidden_capability git_push.
Agent_untrusted has forbidden_capability workflow_modify.
Agent_untrusted has forbidden_capability network_egress.
Agent_untrusted has forbidden_capability file_write.

% maintainer_mutation has no flat forbids: workflow mutation is gated
% per-action by c7_workflow_mutation_needs_approval below.

% ── derived session predicates ────────────────────────────────────────────

% Untrusted input reached the session (spec §Taint Propagation).
E is tainted_session if E is instruction_tainted.
E is tainted_session if E has prompt_trust L and L is an untrusted_level.
E is tainted_session if E has source_trust L and L is an untrusted_level.
E is tainted_session if E is edited_after_trigger.

% Ambient credentials are present in the runtime.
E is secret_bearing if E has secret C and C is a critical_secret.

% A secret has actually flowed into session data.
E is secret_exposed if E has taint C and C is a critical_secret.

% Tainted by untrusted input or by secret access (D5 wording).
E is compromised_session if E is tainted_session.
E is compromised_session if E is secret_exposed.

% D1 exposure: untrusted input present, or ambient credentials to steal.
E is at_risk if E is tainted_session.
E is at_risk if E is secret_bearing.

% Runtime-secret surfaces (D1): procfs environ plus credential-bearing
% process state. '*' spans path segments, so /proc/self/environ and
% /proc/1/task/2/environ both match.
T is a procfs_secret_path if T is like "/proc/*/environ".
T is a procfs_secret_path if T is like "/proc/*/status".
T is a procfs_secret_path if T is like "/proc/*/cmdline".

% Destination explicitly approved for a secret class (D2 allowlist).
E is cleared_for C if E has destination Dst and Dst is approved_for C.

% Command / tool allowlist hits (D3).
E is exec_safelisted if E has target Cmd and Cmd is a safe_command.
E is tool_safelisted if E has target Tool and Tool is a safe_tool.

% Events whose principal acts under a reviewed manifest (D6).
E is manifest_scoped if E has actor_trust reviewed_skill.
E is manifest_scoped if E has actor_trust reviewed_mcp.
E is capable_of A if E has capability A.

% GitHub App presented an immutable app id (incident rule 1).
E is app_identified if E has actor_app_id Id.

% ── mandatory deny rules D1–D6 (spec §Mandatory Deny Rules) ──────────────

% id: d1_procfs_secret_read
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and D has action file_read and E has target T and T is a procfs_secret_path and E is at_risk.

% id: d2_secret_to_untrusted_sink
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and D has action A and A is a sink_kind and E has taint C and C is a critical_secret and E is not cleared_for C.

% id: d3_tainted_exec
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and D has action command_exec and E is tainted_session and E is not exec_safelisted.

% id: d3_tainted_tool_call
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and D has action tool_call and E is tainted_session and E is not tool_safelisted.

% id: d4_tainted_github_write
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and D has action A and A is a github_write_kind and E is tainted_session.

% id: d5_tainted_workflow_mutation
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and D has action A and A is a mutation_kind and E is compromised_session and E is not human_approved.

% id: d6_capability_mismatch
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and D has action A and E is manifest_scoped and E is not capable_of A.

% ── incident-specific reference rules (spec §Incident-Specific Reference
%    Policy: these alone block the June 2026 exploit chain) ───────────────

% id: i1_unallowlisted_github_app
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and E has actor_type github_app and E has actor_app_id Id and Id is not a trusted_app.

% id: i1_unallowlisted_github_app
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and E has actor_type github_app and E is not app_identified.

% id: i2_agent_mode_untrusted_trigger
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and E has exec_mode agent and E has source_trust L and L is not same_as trusted_human.

% id: i3_procfs_environ_read
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and D has action file_read and E has target T and T is like "/proc/*/environ".

% id: i4_oidc_taint_to_sink
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and D has action A and A is an oidc_exfil_kind and E has taint oidc_exchange_credential.

% id: i5_idtoken_grant_untrusted_trigger
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and E has permission "id-token:write" and E has source_trust L and L is not same_as trusted_human.

% id: i6_profile_forbidden_action
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and D has action A and E has profile P and P has forbidden_capability A.

% id: i6_profile_forbidden_tool
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and E has profile P and E has tool T and P has forbidden_capability T.

% id: i6_profile_forbidden_capability
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and E has profile P and E has capability C and P has forbidden_capability C.

% id: i7_edited_after_trigger
D has outcome deny if D has subject E and E is edited_after_trigger.

% ── gated outcomes ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

% Shell is a privileged capability: never plain-allowed, always sandboxed
% (spec §Tool Wrappers). Tainted exec is already denied by d3 above.
% id: sandboxed_exec
D has outcome allow_with_sandbox if D has subject E and E is an event and D has action command_exec.

% Tainted sessions write files only inside a sandbox (memory/config files
% are sinks that influence later agent behavior, spec §Sinks).
% id: sandboxed_tainted_write
D has outcome allow_with_sandbox if D has subject E and D has action file_write and E is tainted_session.

% Ambient secrets present: sink payloads must be redacted before leaving
% the runtime (spec §Secret Handling). Actual secret taint is denied by d2.
% id: redact_sink_with_ambient_secrets
D has outcome allow_with_redaction if D has subject E and D has action A and A is a sink_kind and E is secret_bearing.

% Workflow-file mutation always needs a per-action human approval, even in
% trusted sessions (spec conformance test 7).
% id: c7_workflow_mutation_needs_approval
D has outcome require_confirmation if D has subject E and E is an event and D has action workflow_modify and E is not human_approved.

% id: approved_workflow_mutation
D has outcome allow if D has subject E and D has action workflow_modify and E is human_approved.

% New skills, MCP connections, and secret materialization are gated on a
% human until trust registries land (spec §MCP and Skill Controls,
% §Secret Handling).
% id: gate_skill_install
D has outcome require_confirmation if D has subject E and E is an event and D has action skill_install.

% id: gate_mcp_connect
D has outcome require_confirmation if D has subject E and E is an event and D has action mcp_connect.

% id: gate_secret_materialize
D has outcome require_confirmation if D has subject E and E is an event and D has action secret_materialize.

% ── baseline allow ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
% Low-risk kinds are allowed when nothing above outranks; unknown action
% kinds match no rule and the gate fails closed (NO_MATCHING_POLICY).

% id: baseline_allow
D has outcome allow if D has subject E and E is an event and D has action A and A is a baseline_allowed_kind.
